<paragraph blockId="172.[151,1437,321,744]" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,538,564]" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Remarks:</emphasis>
A.H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark" box="[390,537,538,564]" firstAuthor="Clark" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" pagination="371 - 377" refId="ref176404" refString="Clark, A. H. (1949) Echinoderms from the mid-Atlantic dredged by lhe Atlantis in the summer of 1948. Journal of the Washington Academy of Sciences, 39, 371 - 377." type="journal article" year="1949">Clark (1949)</bibRefCitation>
reported this species from the Azores, based fragments of two medium-sized specimens retrieved by 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Seamount (A. H. Clark" authorityYear="1949" box="[413,500,574,600]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Atlantis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[413,500,574,600]" italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Atlantis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, west of S„o Miguel Island (cruise 152, sta 20: 
<geoCoordinate box="[1025,1165,573,600]" degrees="37" direction="north" minutes="50" orientation="latitude" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" precision="15" seconds="30" value="37.841667">37°50’30”N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[1175,1318,574,600]" degrees="26" direction="west" minutes="00" orientation="longitude" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" precision="15" seconds="00" value="-26.0">26°00’00”W</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity box="[1329,1424,573,600]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.562" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" unit="m" value="2.562">2,562 m</quantity>
). Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Serafy" box="[222,376,610,636]" firstAuthor="Serafy" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" pagination="41 - 48" refId="ref199987" refString="Serafy, D. K. (1974) A new heart-urchin, Araeolampas atlantica, new genus, new species, from the North Atlantic and notes on the closely related Homolampas. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 87, 41 - 48." type="journal article" year="1974">Serafy (1974)</bibRefCitation>
re-examined one of the specimens and assigned it to his newly described species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="$ Serafy" authorityYear="1974" class="Echinoidea" family="Loveniidae" genus="Araeolampas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spatangoida" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Araeolampas atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The second specimen of H.L. Clark was not mentioned by Serafy, but it seems likely that this also was an 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serafy" authorityYear="1974" box="[151,300,682,708]" class="Echinoidea" family="Loveniidae" genus="Araeolampas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spatangoida" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,300,682,708]" italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Araeolampas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, since 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Agassiz" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[380,495,682,708]" class="Echinoidea" family="Maretiidae" genus="Homolampas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spatangoida" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis box="[380,495,682,708]" italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">H. fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not reach a size larger than 
<quantity box="[870,949,681,708]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="35.0">35 mm</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Serafy" box="[964,1103,682,708]" firstAuthor="Serafy" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" pagination="41 - 48" refId="ref199987" refString="Serafy, D. K. (1974) A new heart-urchin, Araeolampas atlantica, new genus, new species, from the North Atlantic and notes on the closely related Homolampas. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 87, 41 - 48." type="journal article" year="1974">Serafy 1974</bibRefCitation>
) and confirmed records of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Agassiz" baseAuthorityYear="1869" class="Echinoidea" family="Maretiidae" genus="Homolampas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spatangoida" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">H. fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are restricted to the West Atlantic.
</paragraph>
